In {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 2 ({{ill|1869|en|1869|qid=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}}), a shrine building was constructed on the site by domain lord {{ill|Kuroda Nagatomo|en|Kuroda Nagatomo|qid=Q6446276|lt=Kuroda Nagachika|1=Kuroda Nagatomo}}. In {{ill|Taishō era|en|Taishō era|qid=Q329174|lt=Taishō|1=Taishō era}} 8 ({{ill|1919|en|1919|qid=Q2157|lt=1919|1=1919}}), the {{ill|Haniyasu Shrine|ja|埴安神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haniyasu Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|qid=Q135579707|1=Haniyasu Shrine}}, the local tutelary shrine of Nanakuma, was relocated and merged here. On March 16, {{ill|Taishō era|en|Taishō era|qid=Q329174|lt=Taishō|1=Taishō era}} 11 ({{ill|1922|en|1922|qid=Q2165|lt=1922|1=1922}}), Kikuchi Shrine was officially designated as a {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q712534}}, and on April 4, {{ill|Shōwa era|en|Shōwa era|qid=Q327567|lt=Shōwa|1=Shōwa era}} 8 ({{ill|1933|en|1933|qid=Q18726|lt=1933|1=1933}}), it was promoted to the status of a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|1=Ken-sha|qid=Q90139226}}{{efn|Ken-sha|qid=Q90139226|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q712534}}. On April 7, it was designated as a shrine receiving government offerings, and on April 13, the grand 600th anniversary festival of Taketoki's death was held.

